Nevertheless, the Chamber of Deputies approved Wednesday the proposals of the left transfers of money and has increased the rewards of officials, the functioning of social services and direct payments to farmers. 
The government blamed the proposals of Social Democrats the fact that they would increase indirectly the budget deficit. 
For this reason, a violent disagreement arose between the left on the one hand, the government, Klaus and right on the other hand, disagreement which calls into question the future of Fischer, who had been trained by agreement between the ODS, the ČSSD and the Green Party. 
Critics argue that the budget, as it was voted by members, removes the package of savings spent by the government of Fischer and according to stem the indebtedness of the state. 
Klaus, who can ratify the law on the state budget but that there is no requirement, said today at a breakfast discussion with entrepreneurs, that policies have long neglected the "serious problem" of the "disability irréfrénable" of public finances. 
Now there is, according to him, no positive solution. 
Only a strong government could bring an improvement, if he could rely on a consensus of political parties, according to the president. 
The president of the ODS Mirek Topolánek has indicated that the budget is staggering and that the government should call into question its existence. 
The Vice-President of the ODS Petr Nečas told the ČTK that the idea of a Cabinet administrative supported by the ČSSD, ODS and the Greens is clearly more. 
In its response, the Prime Minister Fischer described such words of "drastic ". 
The head of the ČSSD Jiří Paroubek reacted to Topolánek, saying that the budget deficit prepared for this year by the former government of Topolánek is staggering and that it will exceed 200 billion kronor. 
On Wednesday, the ČSSD called a success the ratification of the state budget for the next year. 
The People's Party was also satisfied. 
Morgan Freeman will play Mandela in Clint Eastwood's new film 
Despite criticism of the fact that the main roles are played by American actors, South Africans say that the new Hollywood film Invictus - Invaincu will present to the world a lot about the country, its struggles and victories. 
The history of sport, relations between races and Nelson Mandela. 
Morgan Freeman, American actor rewarded the Oscars, embodies the film on the life of Nelson Mandela, tireless fighter against the racist apartheid regime in South Africa and first black president. 
Freeman said, that this is a Mandela aged ninety-one years who asked him to embody in the film. 
Matt Damon plays an important role. 
I told him: "If I must embody, I should be able to see you personally. 
The actor aged seventy-two years old who was awarded a prize for his role in the drama Milion Dollar Baby of Clint Eastwood located in the middle of boxing has, for example, embodied the leader of a movement against slavery become itself slave, a fictional U.S. president, even God in the film Evan Almighty but never someone still alive and so important to so many people as Mandela. 
The ex-homme of state South African was imprisoned 27 years for his hard work in favour of the end of apartheid in South Africa. 
He was released in 1990 and became president of the country for four years. 
In 1993 he was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize. 
Invictus is a Latin word meaning unbeaten and this is the title of a poem by the English author William Ernest Henley published in 1875. 
The challenge was to speak with him. 
The film tells the true story of joint efforts of Nelson Mandela and the captain of the South African rugby team François to unify the country. The newly elected President Mandela knows that his country resteencore and always divided racially and economically after apartheid. 
It is sure to unite his people through sport and decides to unite the rugby players who are among the outsiders in the world. 
The South African team will eventually move in World Cup in 1995. 
Freeman has worked a few years to bring the history of Mandela on screen. 
I had no other purpose if not play this role to the of the reality, said Freeman. 
The biggest challenge for me it was of course, talk like him 
The actor said that if he and the politician international were in the same region, it would have tried to meet Mandela, dinner with him, to be behind the scenes before his speech. 
The most important thing for him was to shake his hand. 
I realized that when I give you my hand, I recover your energy, it is transmitted and I had the impression of how you feel, "he said. 
It is important for me to try to become another person. 
Matt Damon plays in the film François Pienaar, captain of a national rugby team in which there is a majority of white players. 
The actor said that he had six months to prepare for a role in the harsh environment of rugby. 
For him, his first meeting with Pienaar at his home was a great surprise. 
I remember when I come to the door of the house, I opened and the first thing I said to Francois Pienaar was: "I have the air much greater in the film ". 
Despite the differences between the actors and models, Invictus under the leadership of director Eastwood received positive opinions and there is even talk of ambitions for the Oscars. 
The film critic Todd McCarthy newspaper Daily Variety summarized his appreciation in these words: "This is a very good story, a film very well done." 
In the evaluations of films on the site rottentomatoes. Com, Invictus received 76 percent of positive feedback. 
The mystery of the will in Norway is resolved: the Russians tested a rocket 
There has been a strange light phenomenon of unknown origin over Norway. 
The Russian Ministry of Defence has recognized that yesterday have tested a rocket intercontinental ballistic missile near the Norwegian border. 
The launch has still been a failure and the missile "Bulava" which was originally to be the pride of the Russian army is gradually becoming the nightmare of Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimir Putin. 
His presence repeated tests of the rocket has not had the desired effect on the success of test flights. 
Most of the time, Bulava has not disappeared, or it was damaged in flight. 
The Russian newspapers speak of "Bulava" as "missile which do not steal" 
A missile that do not steal but shining 
This 13th test took place at the beginning. 
It is only at the end of the flight that there was further damage to equipment. 
This is clearly the engine of the third floor of the rocket that exploded. 
This time, "Bulava" is soaring nuclear submarine Dmitrij Donskij which was sailing under the surface of the White Sea. 
This type of missile can be fired from a moving boat and submerged 
That is why the mysterious light above Norway caused by an unidentified flying object precisely the was by a "Bulava" flawed. 
Moreover, the Norwegians have not doubted a moment that it is a Russian rocket. 
The generals argue that this time, we cannot talk of failure. 
The first two stages of the rocket have resisted and damage has affected only the third. 
In previous cases, the engines have experienced failures on the first floor. 
Although none of the test launches happened smoothly, the leadership of the Ministry of Defence considers that only six out of thirteen have been failures. 
This success rate of almost 50 percent fills the general optimism and they therefore always that one day "Bulava" fly without problems and that it will prevail even ten nuclei hypersonic a total weight of 1.15 tonnes. 
The legendary Fetissov to 51 years has signed an one-year contract with CSKA Moscow 
The legendary defender Viatcheslav Fetissov will return in a professional match in 51 years. 
The former world champion, Olympic champion and holder of the Stanley Cup will assist his team of CSKA Moscow in need and will make its entry probablementdéjà during the match Friday against Petrograd. 
Fetissov, which ended his career to forty years in 1998, is currently the President of CSKA. 
After the injury of Denis Kuliash we urgently need another defender. 
Fetissov train regularly and agrees to help the team. 
We must still resolve some details on the form, says the coach of club Sergey Nyemtchinov, quoted by the agency pa. 
It was not clear whether the comeback of legendary hockey player will affect only one match. 
I think that Fetissov is one of those who are able to strengthen the mental other players, "said Nyemtchinov. 
According to AP, in the case of his return on the ice, Fetissov becomes the oldest Russian professional hockey player. 
In NHL, the legendary attacking Gordie Howe played a season for Hartford and scored 15 goals and 26 assists. 
The oldest of the famous quintet Fetissov, Kassatonov - Makarov, Larionov, Krutov is one of the best hockey players and among those with the most success. 
Under the colours of the Soviet Union it has won two gold at the Olympic Games, seven titles of world champion, he has triumphed at the Canada Cup and world Junior Championship. 
In the second part of his career, he picked the tributes also In NHL where twice held the Stanley Cup. 
It is a member since 2001 of the Hockey Hall of Fame. 
Hyundai has listened to the unions and cancels all overtime 
The direction of the Hyundai plant in Nošovice has agreed with unions to cancel all overtime. 
It is precisely because of overtime frequent that unions have declared a state of emergency strike Monday. 
The spokesman Petr Vaněk plant Hyundai has confirmed. 
However, still reach agreement with the unions on a Saturday worked again this year. 
We cannot abandon our production plan, it is essential, that is why voluntary overtime were proposed on Saturday 19 December knowing that there would be two teams, said Vaněk. 
The site Sedmička. Cz indicated that the company has proposed a bonus 400 Czech crowns to employees who would be part of the team on Saturday. 
It will be awarded also afterwards for the day worked on 28 November. 
The company, according to Vaněk, decided to change the way to motivate its employees in exchange for overtime. 
Either they receive the supplement for hours, or they can ask a replacement leave on 28 December and extend their end of year holidays aindiqué Vaněk. 
In addition to this all employees present on Saturday will receive compensation for the costs of transport and for their lunch. 
Given the fact that overtime were the most urgent and the warmest in the comments and the demands of the unions as employees who have ceased spontaneously production last week, management has taken the immediate decision to cancel all overtime for the month of December, said Vaněk. 
Until last week, employees of the automotive plant were forced to work almost daily two overtime in addition to their eight hours. 
The Unions have cancel the state of strike after signing of the agreement. 
The following negotiations between the direction of the car factory and trade unions must take place Friday afternoon. 
The union leader Petr Kuchař said on Wednesday that they were ready to stop the state of strike in cases of agreement on their claims and signing of a common document. 
The situation in the factory culminated last Wednesday when nearly 400 employees started spontaneously on strike because of incessant overtime. 
They also protested against poor conditions of pay and so-called bizutages. 
Management has defended with the fact that employees had to work as a supplement to meet the imperatives of car production. 
At the announcement of the strike Monday, trade unions have also requested that the employees who have ceased production are not subject to any sanction. 
The unions are asking the company to reduce the time spent in overtime to a minimum. 
In addition, they want this year a reward of 5 000 crowns (209 €) for them. 
The automotive plant Hyundai of Nošovice currently employs 2, 000 people. 
She started series production last year in November. 
It has produced about 80, 000 vehicles until September of this year, with a production capacity of 200, 000 cars per year. 
Czech discovery: a substance that operates on the HIV virus "hard-working people" also 
A team of scientists Czech and German is testing new combinations that can slow the spread of HIV in the body. 
The main advantage of the substance improved is that it is also on the viruses that have already developed an immunity to medicines. 
This is, in some cases, the upper hand on the fact that the combination is not as intensely on common variants of the virus as well as some drugs already available. 
It is not possible to cure AIDS at present. 
We can prolong the life of patients through a mixture of drugs that prevent the spread of HIV in the body. 
Their Consumption, however, a series of side effects. 
The repression of this increase is the development of so-called resistant viruses on which drugs have more effect. 
The work of experts of three institutions, the Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic, the VŠCHT Prague and the University of Heidelberg paves the way for a way to deal with the resistance of the virus. 
They have shown that substances called metalocarboranes act on the protein responsible for the proliferation of the HIV virus. 
The metalocarboranes are an assembly of boron, hydrogen, carbon and cobalt. 
This combination is blocking the development of the virus in a different way of all drugs used to date and that is why they could overcome the problem of resistance. 
The work of researchers leads them to discover new substances "improved ", on the basis of their knowledge of the molecular mechanics of their routes on the proteins of the virus. 
The metalocarboranes have a single three-dimensional structure: two cages to multiple walls are formed by the boron atoms of hydrogen and carbon and connected by a metal atom, in this case the cobalt. 
A virus traitor and resistant. 
The HIV protease is a protein of the HIV virus which is essential to the life cycle of the virus. 
Without the division of the HIV virus caused by the HIV protease there would be no birth of mature infectious particles of the virus. 
If we stop the HIV protease, it will stop the spread of the virus in the body of the patient, explain the researchers in a press release issued by the Institute of organic chemistry and biochemistry of the Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic. 
In their work published in the scientific journal of Medicinal Chemistry, scientists describe a series of combinations where two pairs of cages (see table) are connected by a short organic link, which is then systematically amended. 
A little smaller but more reliable. 
The effectiveness of this series of substances on The HIV protease was tested in test tubes and its variants resistant, obtained from patients infected with HIV. 
On the current version of the enzyme, the effect of metalocarboranes is not as strong as on medicines clinics, however it is not diminishing on versions resistant against which current drugs are often ineffective. 
The metalocarboranes, with their unique mechanism of action and their other properties as their biological and chemical stability, low toxicity and the possibility of other chemical changes are therefore interesting combinations to examine more to move towards the development of effective drugs against HIV, says Pavlína řezáčová, director of the laboratory of structural biology of the Institute of organic chemistry and biochemistry and molecular genetics Institute of the Academy of Sciences. 
Dispute around the budget. The ODS is attacking Fischer, who defends 
The president of the Civic Democratic Party (ODS), Mirek Topolánek has described as "staggering" the budget ratified for the following year and according to him, the government of Prime Minister Jan Fischer should question its existence. 
