That said, it should not be expected to support and tolerance of Democrats. 
I have not thought about it and once it will be on the agenda then I will dedicate, said since the House to journalists, the Defence Minister Martin Barták, elected government precisely by Democrats. 
The Prime Minister Fischer has soared in the afternoon for a debate of the European Council in Brussels. 
The ODS has backtracked at the request of the prime minister. 
Nečas stressed at the same time that the ODS would probably have voted Wednesday against the amended budget if he had not specifically asked Members Democrats to allow the vote on the budget. 
We do not have the feeling of being orphans, there is no small children, he responded to the question of whether the ODS had not suffered accusations from the President of the Party in the House or in the country in negotiating the budget. 
I have not noticed that my vote would have been lacking. 
I already knew when I renounced my mandate that what would follow in the coming months would be a bolchévisation of the House and destruction of all that was positive, reacted Topolánek in person. 
According to the new schedules ČD there will be fewer trains for the same charges. 
The Czech railways will remove or limit from 13 December some express trains or regional less responsible and will instead some others. 
The full coverage of transport will fall on the day of entry into force of the new schedules of two percent compared to today. 
Most of the charges will not change, including the basic rates and the reduced fare. 
For example, the inhabitants of the region in Ostrava who will have more connections to the capital, the railways will add a rowing pendolino. 
On the contrary, an express will cease to serve Bratislava. 
There will also be less fast trains on the line Prague - Písek - České Budějovice, the hotline Prague - Letohrad will be drastically reduced. 
At the regional level, the largest decline in transport in the region of Hradec Králové eight percent in total, Prague and its environs can celebrate an increase. 
Two night trains on the line Prague - Tábor - České Budějovice are also cancelled and the movement of some express trains on the line Prague - Písek - České Budějovice is reduced to only a few days in the week. 
Among the biggest changes, we can see the introduction of a new direct line of Milovice in Prague: for the moment the inhabitants of Milovice must change at Lysá nad Labem. 
It is the fifteenth line of suburban Esko, whose opening is possible thanks to the completion of the electrification of the line between Lysá nad Labem and Milovice. 
The distant lines to the capital will have their final destination at the main station in Prague (Praha Hlavní nádraží). 
The ČD will introduce more lines HC Pendolino between Prague and Ostrava and trains to Šumperk / Jeseník will leave by intervals of two hours. 
Travellers can no longer take the Pendolino to Bratislava from 13 December. 
The bill this year for regional railways: 200 million kroner. 
The express trains are ordered and paid by the Department of Transport and will pay the railways next year in all four billion kronor to address the losses visible, the same amount as this year. The regional trains are ordered by the regions who will pay for them by a total of eight billion next year, knowing that the state will participate in height of nearly three billion. 
This year the regional trains are 200 million more expensive. 
The railways have newly signed a contract for ten years, until now the duration was always a year. 
The railways appreciate the system, which also explains that they have not used a price increase of the vast majority of tickets. 
The changes will affect only tickets a day ČD Net and tickets at reduced prices eLiška. 
For travellers without reduction card, the price of ČD Net will increase from 450 to 600 crowns. 
The price of eLiška will depend on the miles, whereas previously it was valid between cities in a region to choice and was a single tariff of 160 crowns. 
The Filipino rebels still hold more than 50 people, children have been released 
The rebels have kidnapped today 75 people in the southern Philippines, including some students of a primary school and their teachers. 
It is the AFP Agency who informed, but who spoke to the origin of 65 hostages only. 
The 17 children were released after eight hours, as well as a primary school teachers. 
The hostage-taking took place in the province of Agusan del Sur. 
It is reported that about 19 rebels have used the hostages as human shields during a flight to the police. 
The local negotiators are trying to find an agreement for the release of the remaining hostages. 
According to the AFP Agency, the rebels belong to the New People's Army (NPA), which is the armed wing of the Communist Party of the Philippines (CPP). 
