Vaccination against pneumococcal will be free and voluntary 
The Vaccination against pneumococcal reverse old habits as early as January. 
It will be the first to be free and at the same time optional for families. 
Some already, saying that a compulsory vaccination would be more effective. 
The preparations for the introduction of free vaccination against pneumococcal peak. 
The Pharmaceutical Institute for vaccines already defines the maximum prices that will pay for health insurance. 
The experts also see clear in the process of vaccination. 
A new vaccination. 
Free vaccines for children of August. 
Since January, children born last year from 2 August can be vaccinated for free against pneumococcal. 
The condition is that they have not yet been vaccinated. 
If we began vaccination last year or earlier, we will have to pay yourself vaccinations. 
The first dose of vaccine should be administered between the third and the fifth month of the child. 
Last year a quarter of families has voluntarily vaccinated their children against pneumococcal. 
Yet parents paid 1600 crowns or even more for a dose. 
The vaccination of younger requires four doses. 
Experts estimate that each year the health insurance spend 300 to 450 000 SEK in doses of vaccine. 
However, they save on medical care that unvaccinated children would require. 
So far the state was spending approximately 500 000 crowns per year for any vaccination of children. 
Vaccination repaid was introduced with the "Janota package ". 
The Pneumococcal are the cause of inflammation of the middle ear but also serious infections including inflammation of the brain and blood poisoning. 
According to surveys in hospitals, there has until 28 deaths of children under 10 years caused by pneumococcal infections. 
Apart from the Czech Republic, about 40 other countries have introduced vaccination refunded. 
The Vaccination will be mandatory? 
There is advice on a possible obligation of vaccination in the future. 
From January, it must be resolved by insurance and optional. 
For example, the president of the association Nahlas Rudolf Kalovský indicated that a compulsory vaccination would be more positive. 
His association has long promoted the vaccination against pneumococcal. 
At an international conference to which our association has participated, experts were not really satisfied with the fact that we have a voluntary vaccination. 
It is not ideal. 
On the other hand, we are pleased to have been able to impose at least this. 
I think it is a direction that we must now follow said Kalovský. 
But the Department of Health does not change the process of vaccination against pneumococcus. 
We are definitely not for the moment, "said his spokesman Vlastimil Sršeň. 
The optional vaccination has its drawbacks, say doctors. 
Hana Cabrnochová, president of the Society of paediatricians, recognizes that a vaccine based on the volontariata its shortcomings. 
If all children were vaccinated, we could consider a reduction of renewals vaccinations "in the situation where the vaccine costs such a sum I understand the decision making vaccination optional" said however Cabrnochová. 
The Experts predict that next year, more than 80 percent of new parents will vaccinate their infants. 
Vaccination against pneumococcal also marks a break from the fact that this is the first vaccination of children which is funded by the insurance and not the state. 
Cabrnochová explains that insurance should free up funds for prevention, they save and on possible future medical care. 
Doctors will have to buy their products themselves 
This is linked to concerns of pediatricians practitioners, concerning the purchase of vaccines. 
The original intention was to purchase vaccines by insurance, doctors receiving the same way as other products of vaccine provided by the state. 
Some Members were concerned, however, that this would allow insurance "deduct the amounts of health insurance." 
Thus, doctors will have to buy the products and wait for the insurance reimburse them. 
According to estimates, pediatricians will individually invest nearly 40 000 SEK per month in vaccines, which is a significant sum. 
It will be far from easy, according to Cabrnochová. 
