And I could ask sacrément more, but I did not do. " 
The member of parliament, millionaire since his former position as an oil trader, has begun to explain its expenditure, in May, after it emerged that he had asked thousands of pounds for his garden before agreeing with the fees office that this "could be considered excessive ". 
An activist has dug a hole in the form of £in the lawn of M Duncan to protest after it was revealed that he had requested 4, 000 GBP for three years. 
Asked about the increase in borrowing, last night, Mr Duncan said: "It was for improvements capitals, approved by the fees office then by Legg." 
He added: "There is no problem of evasion or development or use of rules or anything. 
It was quite clear, in the rules, authorized, etc. 
This could not be clearer or more simple. " 
Faithful, come all see the Advent calendar of Brighton 
The cabs of Brighton beach have found a new way of promotion for the winter months, an interactive Advent calendar. 
Beyond, a group of church alternative that encourages the spiritual exploration by the creativity, invited 24 owners to decorate their cabin for each day of December, using as a theme, songs of Noel. 
The event began on 1 December, while visitors were allowed to visit the last cabin, from 5.30 pm to 6.30 p. m., every day, with blocks and wine served free of charge. 
The songs of Noel selected so far include "I Saw Three Ships, O Come, O Come, Emmanuel and the First Christmas ", for which the cabin presents the work of Janette Tozer, a local artist. 
Martin Poole, 50, an assistant marketing TV of Hove, is a priest of the Diocese of Chichester and Director of Beyond. 
He said: "We want religion is closer to the people in a society post-chrétienté. 
