In this case, do we want to send the message, not only to (Roman Polanski) but also to other accused, that it is possible to escape?, asked Ms. Asayama. 
For her, the filmmaker "request a favour to the court, while scorning its authority ". 
One of the three judges - who now have 90 days to make their decision - underlined "that there were other alternatives to the flight ". 
Mr. Hummel was not the only one to request the abandonment of prosecutions against Roman Polanski. 
The lawyer of Samantha Geimer, the victim, has also claimed, once again, the end of proceedings. 
Recalling that his client no longer supports to be harassed every rebound of the Polanski case, she added: "Nobody in this room can say that the procedure was fair. 
