Hervé Morin has publicly announced its intention to recover the acronym UDF, ruling that François Bayrou did not deserve to defend his political legacy after he reached out to the left. 
The minister of defence, whose party is a partner of the UMP, had planned to confirm this strategy Saturday before the National Council of NC. 
To support his approach, he has received the support of Mr Hervé de Charette (ex-UMP past in NC) which claims ownership of the mark UDF for being the first to file in 2004 at the National Institute of Industrial Property. 
But Friday evening, the office of the association UDF, controlled by the friends of François Bayrou who do not intend to be deprived, has emerged from his silence to launch a formal notice to the Minister and MP, instructing them not to use the acronym and transmit the ownership of the mark, under penalty of prosecution. 
You have multiplied in recent days, the statements indicating that you would suggest to your political movement of + resume + the acronym UDF, writing the association in a letter signed by 19 of the 24 members of the office, including François Bayrou and Marielle de Sarnez the modem, as well as Senator Jean Arthuis centrist Alliance. 
You have also seen fit to follow up on your equipment activist and on the front page of your site, the name of this movement, the New centre +, the slogan + the UDF today +, also see the signatories of the letter. 
As you know, you have no right to the use of this acronym, explains the office of the UDF that remains the NC to withdraw "immediately the mention of the name of the UDF of any medium and (his) website ". 
It also calls on Mr Hervé de Charette "to convey the property of (the) marks its legitimate right holders ". 
If you do not, the courts would be seized to enforce the law and the legitimate rights of members of the UDF, prevent the signatories. 
In their letter they specify that the UDF "is a full-fledged political movement since 1978" and recalled that Mr Morin and his friends had "made the choice" to leave in 2007 "to create a movement competitor, as others had done in 2002, to create the UMP ". 
The New centre has therefore, according to them, no right to use the acronym UDF (Union for French Democracy). 
They also recall that the last congress of the UDF voted in 2007 its accession to the modem for three years and the creation of an office to defend "the material and moral interests" training founded by Valéry Giscard d'Estaing. 
As for Mr Hervé de Charette, continues the bureau, "when he filed the mark ", it was" more adherent of the UDF for three years ", but the UMP. 
It benefits scandalously and fraudulently of the absence of filing of the acronym UDF to conduct on its behalf. 
This brutality is turning into crime, dénoncent-ils, before ironiser on the strategy of NC: "it seems to us that in politics, as in life, it is more worthy to make a name for yourself to try to break the anonymity fraudulently taking a name which was not right ". 
Case Liliane Bettencourt: François-Marie Banier will be judged for abuse of weakness 
The court of Nanterre decided Friday to judge the artist François-Marie Banier to determine if, as in accuses the daughter of the billionaire Liliane Bettencourt, it has benefited from a state of weakness of the octogenarian to rob a portion of his fortune. 
The photographer 62 years, known for his photos of stars, will be judged on 15 and 16 April 2010 for abuse of weakness, an offence punishable by a maximum penalty of three years imprisonment and a fine of €375, 000. 
This decision means that there will be a trial in this case worthy of a saga on one of the richest families of France, in which mother and daughter will snap while taking the reins of the L'Oreal cosmetics empire. 
But the 15th criminal chamber also ordered that a medical expertise of Liliane Bettencourt, aged 87 years old, should be carried out collectively by three doctors. 
The heir and principal shareholder of L'Oréal has always refused to submit to such a review, at least not in the conditions proposed by the prosecution of Nanterre during the investigation. 
Doctors Designated Friday will submit a report before 10 March 2010 by saying whether Liliane Bettencourt could find themselves in a state of weakness and what periods. 
I think it will. 
I will speak to him, said the of the hearing counsel for Mrs Bettencourt, Georges Kiejman. 
For its part, the lawyer of Françoise Bettencourt-Meyers, Olivier Metzner, welcomed the decision of the court. 
This is excellent news (...) the expertise will show that he (Mr Banier) has handled this elderly lady that we must protect, he said. 
For two years, the only daughter of Liliane Bettencourt has committed criminal proceedings against François-Marie Banier, photographer and artist hands-on, which it accuses of having benefited for years from the weakness of his mother to obtain a billion euros of donations, in the form of cheques, life insurance contracts or tables of. 
For its part, Liliane Bettencourt has always denied having been manipulated by the photographer, as a long-standing friend. 
While the court should examine the admissibility of the action taken by Ms. Bettencourt-Meyers, the pleadings of lawyers have sometimes turned to unpacking family Friday. 
Thus, counsel Liliane Bettencourt reported three letters sent by his client (in 1999, 2003 and 2005) to his notary, in which she said beware of the husband of Françoise Bettencourt-Meyers. 
In the letter dated 2003, Liliane Bettencourt added, according to the lawyer: "Could you explain to my daughter that I wrote to Banier once, twice a day for 15 years. 
Françoise, I have never been able to speak to him since his marriage ". 
For its part, the prosecutor in Nanterre again suggested that the complainant was not admissible to act, especially as a guardianship judge has refused in recent days to grant his request to open a procedure of judicial protection for his mother. 
Liliane Bettencourt "has full capacity to act, it is not under protection and has no guardian. 
No one else has to act in his place, "said the representative of the public prosecutor, Marie-Chrsitine Daubigney. 
The court has finally decided that it would decide once the trial will be held on the admissibility of Mrs Bettencourt-Meyers. 
Revolution Managerial or end of economic intelligence? 
If nothing changes in the governance of large French companies, our struggle for the development of the economic intelligence will have been in vain... 
For more than a decade, the attitude of the management of large companies vis-à-vis its employees, recalls the position vis-à-vis consumers before the revolution marketing: it is to join the staff to "values" determined from above as it was once, to impose the consumer products designed by the technicians of the plant. 
By putting the customer at the heart of the company, the revolution has provided marketing strategies of conquest of markets to the... Although the authoritarian temptation to impose products disconnected factors of preferences of clienteles return regularly! 
A demobilization of employees can lead to A deadly demoralisation. 
The suicides at France Telecom, PSA and Renault are only the tip of a much more general phenomenon which affects in particular. 
This demobilization seriously undermines the development of all intellectual functions of the company, including of R D and, more importantly, the economic intelligence. 
Indeed, the IE "requires of all stakeholders (...) a proactive approach and a forward-looking vision "; it requires on the part of employees a commitment that the revenue management authoritarian bedevil completely. 
That is why we call for a managerial revolution that would put the staff at the centre of the concerns of the company as the client. 
The usefulness any opinion surveys internal 
The internal opinion surveys as the questionnaire submitted by Orange to its salariés- will encourage this revolution in managerial practices? 
Unfortunately, I fear not. 
- Firstly because I could see that, faced with a new situation, any structure is finally, after many detours, priority... What it has always done.! 
- Secondly, because authoritarianism - a pathologies of pouvoir- increases in proportion to the importance of its own failures. 
- Finally, because most of the leaders have a simplistic view of human behaviour. 
From the major engineering schools, they have a mechanistic interpretation of psychology. 
They adopt, by intellectual comfort, the old theory Behavioriste, cranked up recently by the "neuroscience" American and widely disseminated, without their knowledge, by the institutes and the media. 
Thus, suggesting that it is possible to handle the "levers" (sic) the commitment of managers, a recent survey by Ipsos published in Le Figaro. Fr conforte-t-elle leaders in a mechanistic governance posture, unsuited to today's world. 
Identify and measure the factors of mobilization 
On the contrary, the managerial revolution necessary for the proper functioning of modern enterprises, to adopt a finalist vision of human behaviour. 
It is to integrate, in any reasoning or practice of governance, a fundamental observation: for employees, the commitment to the company is possible only if it is clear as a means of achieving a portion of their dreams, their ambitions, their projects. 
Currently, only studies from the analysis motifonctionnelle adopt this design of the motivations of employees. 
These studies have shown that they consider their company based on a predetermined doxa which allows them through their image of the company, to assess what it offers them to achieve their life projects. 
Through the identification and measurement of these factors of mobilization, business leaders can control, predict and anticipate their "social performance" and submit their management of human resources "to the place ". 
They create a breeding ground for joint development of a robust and effective economic intelligence. 
Oslo speech: the "just war" is right to praise Obama 
The American right has welcomed Friday speech the eve in Oslo by Barack Obama, satisfied that the Nobel Peace Prize 2009 has defended the concept of "just war" against the enemies of the United States. 
The Conservatives, who had brocardé the award to Mr Obama on 9 October, applauded this time the presidential speech, like Sarah Palin, former candidate for the vice-presidency in the 2008 elections. 
I liked what he said, "said Mrs Palin, égérie of the right wing of the Republican Party daily, USA Today, adding she herself addressed the theme of war" sometimes necessary "in his memoirs that have just been published. 
The war is obviously the last thing in my opinion that Americans want to do, but it is necessary. 
We must stop these terrorists everything out there, she said. 
Mr Obama, who has inherited two wars from his predecessor George W. Bush in Iraq and Afghanistan, has worked Thursday to Oslo to justify the use of force, a way to explain his decision to send 30, 000 additional troops in Afghanistan nine days earlier. 
Another opponent of Mr Obama, Newt Gingrich, said that the president had done in Oslo "a very good job ". 
I found that the speech was really very well, welcomed the former speaker of the House of Representatives, which has particularly appreciated the reference to "the existence of evil in the world" in the presidential. 
By some side, I found this quite historic, "said Mr. Gingrich, interviewed on the radio program" the takeaway ". 
The former elected, regarded by some as a possible candidate for the Republican nomination for the 2012 presidential election, said he was delighted to have seen "a left-wing president" remind members of the Nobel Committee "that they would not be free and could not put a price of peace if the use of force did not exist ". 
For Michael Gerson, former pen of George W. Bush converted columnist at the Washington Post, Mr. Obama delivered "a very American ". 
In addition to appear in "citizen of the world" as "it always does," he spoke as an American president, "reminding Europeans" that they live in a bubble of security that they have not created and that they do little to preserve it, "said Mr Gerson. 
Among the few right to not be convinced, a hawk in the Bush era, the former ambassador to the United Nations John Bolton, called the speech "dull, ampoulé and without inspiration" on the site National Review Online. 
Has the left of the president, the Democrat Dennis Kucinich was alarmed to see Barack Obama justify the use of force. 
When envelope the war in the concept of justice, can easily justify the killing of innocent people, he warned. 
The centre-left press remained however commendation to the president. 
The Los Angeles Times, while continuing to believe that the Nobel prize was awarded prematurely to Mr Obama, described his speech "blockbuster" even for a speaker known for his talent. 
The speech Oslo "should serve as a road map to guide international decisions against conflicts, poverty and oppression ", has ignited the Daily Californian. 
Mr Obama "delivered the speech that he was," said the New York Times, saying "both dark and inspiring ". 
Road: three marathons for an agreement that saves the supplies of Christmas 
After three sessions of négociations-marathon, the road sector unions and employers' organisation TLF, only to be stayed until the end, arrived Friday evening to an agreement that puts an end to the strike and the threat to supplies of Christmas. 
At the meeting of signatures Friday evening, the secretary of state for transport, Dominique Bussereau, was "pleased" of this agreement, after several rounds of negotiations, launched on Wednesday morning. 
After a second night of discussions the negotiators were left in the early morning Friday, with the hope of signing quickly in late morning the text of agreement. 
Even if three employers' organisations (FNTR, Unostra, OTRE) had slammed the door. 
But it took more than six hours of a meeting began at 11.00 for everyone to agree and that the text is signed. 
The conflict "would have been very damaging for business" and "it was feared that it will disrupt the Christmas years," said Mr Bussereau. 
The text provides for a wage increase of 4% for the lowest wages (in road transport local and regional), and 2.9% for the highest (international transport). 
In hourly rate, for the bas-salaires, "from 8.72 euros to 9.06. 
It is not much, but it is very far, explained Patrice Clos (FO). 
It will give the order to our activists that there is no blockages, no blockade of centres of supplies. 
But we can always have some recalcitrant who are not happy, he added. 
Philippe Grillot, president of TLF, welcomed "a good agreement ", even if it was" difficult to concede the increases on high salaries given the international competition ". 
According to him, the increases will be of the order of EUR 170 monthly for low wages and 100 to 120 euros for the highest. 
It is the agreement of common sense and respect of employees, "said Maxime Dumont (CFDT), while Thierry Douine (CFTC) welcomed" a historic agreement ". 
Richard Jaubert (CGT) has mentioned "an acceptable compromise ". 
The agreement also provides for the upgrading of travel expenses of 3%, and the holding of general state of road transport in the first half of 2010, which will address the issue of a 13th month and modernization of the collective agreement. 
Mr Bussereau recalled that "a decrease of EUR 100 million in employers' contributions" has been the subject of a government amendment to draft amending finance for 2009, voted in the night from Thursday to Friday by the National Assembly. 
The government will ask the Senate to vote "in identical ". 
The signing of TLF allows that the agreement applies initially businesses adherent to this organization, and in a second time, the entire profession, in the case of an extension by the Minister of Labour. 
It will be "as soon as possible," assured Mr Bussereau. 
The opposition of employers' organisations can only delay the process. 
The FNTR denounced a "fool's bargain ", because the EUR 100 million" had already been promised the sector to offset a portion of the carbon tax ". 
The Secretary of state for transport has obliged us to negotiate in the urgency, not in conclusion d? A shared analysis, but not to thwart the turkey eaters of the next eve, deplored the Unostra. 
For the Otre, the agreement risk "digging the grave d? A very large number of SMEs in the sector in the next 12 months ". 
RER A: disruption this weekend, unions unhappy with proposals of the RATP 
The disturbances on the RER a, the largest urban transit line of France, will continue during the weekend, while a meeting Friday at the 2nd day of strike between unions and management of the RATP left on their hunger on their demand for premium. 
Saturday and Sunday, for this important weekend of purchases before Christmas, there will be no trains between 10 a. m., a train on two on the central portion (between Defence and Nation) and a train on four outside the central section. 
The interconnection with SNCF will be suspended at Nanterre Prefecture, which will require passengers to change trains. 
The Galeries Lafayette, who expect 200, 000 customers every day, welcomed the fact that "the RATP should make efforts to serve the department stores ". 
The RER A crosses from west to east The Paris conurbation. 
The RATP short of Saint-Germain-en-Laye and Nanterre to Boissy-Saint-Léger and Marne-la-Vallée. 
Friday, about a train on two was circulated at peak hours, and almost no rowing in off-peak hours, as planned. 
As Thursday, there has been no crowds on the docks, Franciliens organized. 
And in the morning, the station of Saint-Germain-en-Laye (Yvelines) was much less crowded than usual, especially because of the absence of school students. 
Has Boissy-Saint-Léger (Val-de-Marne), Jack Nbakina, engineer of 29 years, explained to be lifted "a hour and A half earlier, so be sure to arrive on time ". 
The station Saint-Lazare has not been saturation, indicated the SNCF, which had provided a framework of agents and security forces. 
The RER A operated by the SNCF from or to Cergy-Le-Haut arrived or left the station Saint-Lazare to join the subways. 
New general assemblies of strikers will be held Saturday and Sunday, which will review the results, deemed "meagre" by the unions, a meeting with management on Friday afternoon. 
The director of RSP proposes to negotiate a specific protocol for the RER an on all aspects, working time, career path etc. 
This is not what the drivers, who are demanding a premium due, according to Thierry Garon (South). 
The RATP puts even its proposals for premium in brackets, has outraged the CGT, stressing that the direction "was not kaput to solve a problem while among road and the SNCF is done ". 
A new meeting is planned Monday for "a broader review of the conditions of exercise of the profession," said the RATP. 
What has also say the unions that the company "scoffed users over the weekend ". 
In the morning, some 150 drivers had invaded a committee of establishment at headquarters in Paris. 
It was then that the direction, which refused until then any discussion during the strike, had suggested "in a spirit of appeasement" the meeting. 
The conflict threatens to widen the RER B Tuesday, after the filing of a notice by Unsa and Independents. 
The trade unions demand a premium of 120 euros (Unsa) to EUR 150 and EUR 30 variables (CGT, FO, CFDT, South, independent) and complain about the deterioration of working conditions on this line the million daily passengers. 
Drivers of RER, all in the second part of career, affect 2.200 to 2.700 euros gross as well as 600 to 650 euros of premiums, for the shifts, Sundays and holidays. 
The Turkish justice dissolved the pro-Kurdish party, decision with serious consequences 
The Turkish Constitutional Court ruled Friday the dissolution of the country's main pro-Kurdish party, a decision that was immediately followed by expressions of anger in the Kurdish community, in the south-east of the country and in Istanbul. 
This decision could greatly complicate the task of the government, which is to reach out to the Kurdish community to try to end 25 years of conflict. 
The Democratic Society Party (DTP) was dissolved because it had become a "home of activities detrimental to the independence of the state and its indivisible unity," said the press the president of the court Hasim Kiliç, at the end of four days of deliberations. 
The decision was taken unanimously of 11 judges, while a qualified majority of seven votes was required to deliver the dissolution, said Mr Kiliç, adding that 37 of party officials, including its president Ahmet Türk and member Aysel Tugluk, are banned from politics for five years. 
The judge also announced the lifting of parliamentary immunity enjoyed by Mr. Türk and Mrs Tugluk and confiscation by the Treasury of the party. 
The DTP has 21 seats in Parliament (550). 
Its leaders had warned before the verdict that members would leave Parliament rather than sit as parliamentarians without label. 
The decision follows a procedure launched in 2007 by the prosecutor of the Court of Cassation Abdurrahman Yalçinkaya, who accuses the DTP to obey "directives" of the Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK), considered a terrorist organisation by Ankara and many countries. 
Many observers believe that the DTP is the showcase legal policy of PKK rebels. 
The party maintains, however, that it was "no organic links" with the PKK but refuses to call it a terrorist organization and calls on the government to negotiate with him. 
The verdict of the Court comes at a time when the government is to reach out to the Kurdish community in proposing a series of measures strengthening its rights, to try to shrink the support of the PKK and put an end to the conflict. 
The leaders of the DTP had said that a dissolution could lead to a resurgence of tensions in the south-east Anatolia, where many demonstrations against the conditions of detention of the PKK leader Abdullah Öcalan have degenerated into clashes with police in recent weeks. 
After the announcement of justice, a thousand demonstrators gathered in front of the DTP in Diyarbakir, the largest city in southeast populated majority of Kurds. 
The security forces fired tear gas and used water cannons, while protesters threw Molotov cocktails or stones, with slingshots. 
A hundred people demonstrated also in Istanbul. 
After the verdict, Mr Türk said that the decision of Justice would "deepen the despair." 
Turkey cannot resolve this issue (Kurdish, Ed) by banning a party, he said to the press. 
The government, formed by a party from the Islamist movement, also deplored the decision. 
We are opposed in principle to the closure of parties. 
This resolves nothing, "said Minister of Energy Taner Yildiz. 
This decision is a total torpedoing of democratic openness launched by the government, "said political analyst Ahmet Insel. 
We can expect, of course, a reaction from the PKK, he added. 
On Thursday, the PKK has claimed an attack that had killed seven soldiers three days earlier in the north of Turkey, one of the most deadly in recent months. 
The new "Silicon-valley" 
For a long time she had the reputation of city secret, prohibited to Western visitors. 
Zelenograd, one of the ten districts of Moscow, was under the Soviet regime, a place of research secret weapons, under strict supervision. 
Today with its 216 000 inhabitants to 37 km from the centre of Moscow, the municipality has the reputation of being the "Silicon Valley" Soviet. 
Important places of production and of micro- and nanoelectronics are located. 
Since September 2008 representatives of Zelenograd have established links with Riedberg, place of science francfortois - with academic institutions and companies in the centre of innovations in Frankfurt (FIZ). 
There were meetings reciprocal last Wednesday representatives of Zelenograd and Riedberg have ratified a "protocol of close collaboration ". 
The signatories were the Deputy mayor of Moscow Juri Rosljak and the prefect Anatoly Smimov of Zelenograd for the Russian delegation, Edwin Schwarz section chief project for Frankfurt. 
In 2010 representatives of FIZ and SMEs, whose strong point is scientific research, will Zelenograd for a seminar. 
Scientific exchange 
It is a scientific exchange sustainable. 
But also of economic relations. 
It will enable companies of FIZ to enter the Russian market in full expansion. 
Unlike the Russian scientific societies seeking contracts in Germany. 
Zelenograd is the seat of research institutes and companies Soviet famous. 
There is the Institute of Electrical Engineering from Moscow, the big firms Sitronics and Rosssijskaja-Elektronika. 
The municipality was founded in 1958 as "socialist planned city" for research. 
Zelenograd (literal translation "Green City ") gets its name from forested hills in the heart of which research centres are located. 
The project S21: a brake for Stuttgart 
We Cannot place high enough the magnitude of the project Stuttgart 21. 
To its supporters it is nothing less than "new heart of Europe ". 
If you want. S21, it is more than the burial of a railway station, more than a massive construction project that will plunge the heart of the capital of Baden-Württemberg, in a chaos despairing of yards for a decade. 
Stuttgart 21 is born of the spirit of the 1980s. 
The stations head of line, with routes which ended in town, had a reputation at the time to be the relics of the technical transport of the 19th century that were effect of brake shoe modern rail traffic because it was once a lot of time to get the locomotives back to the. 
Arrival, stopping short, departure - that is what needs to be done. 
That is why the head of line must disappear: in Frankfurt and Munich. 
And Stuttgart also: a station of passage of trains, which is about halfway on the trans-European rail between Paris and Budapest / Bratislava where the slogan "heart of Europe ". 
The project S21 will really start, although the visions of the 1980s are no longer compatible with reality. 
Even the most ambitious planners have recognized that the cost to bury the station in the capitals of Hesse and Bavaria, was exorbitant. 
Indeed, the head of line stations no longer pose real problems of entry and exit since there are modern trains, reversible with railcars and voiture-pilote at both ends. 
However, it is now launching the achievement of Stuttgart 21 alongside the new line inter-city towards Ulm. 
The regional and communal policies prevailed. 
The railway company is in part because it is the taxpayer who paid the cost of the risks of the largest infrastructure project of the Federal Republic and not the public company. 
From the point of view planning this project is relatively well justified. 
An urban space which - according to the charts planners generated by computer - will be very green. 
For the system of rail transport the S21 is harmful. 
The station and enlargement of the section are designed for a trafficking which assigned - and this is typical of the 1980s - an enormous growth. 
At the time there was not yet competition from cheap flights. 
The policy of modern traffic should first focus on strengthening the traffic of goods transport by rail is much more environmentally friendly than by truck on the road. 
But the new route, with its inclinations, is not suitable for freight trains. 
The S21, and this is much more serious indirectly affects many other rail projects. 
For example, six billion euros will be swallowed up in the draft of the souabe. 
It is the official figure. 
Experts believe that ten to fifteen billion are more realistic. 
One thing is sure, in the next decade this money will for other junction and congestion in the network. 
The list of the Department of Transportation mentions in all 60 major projects. 
One of the most important is the enlargement of the section across the Rhine Valley of 180 kilometres. 
Since 1987 the line is built in slow motion. 
It would be really urgent support here to build on the fungus. 
But the project S21 had the effect of brake shoe. 
The route of the Rhine Valley is becoming the bottleneck of international freight traffic, and this in the heart of Europe. 
The government is considering the judgment on the airport 
The regional parliament in Wiesbaden, the Land government has raised the possibility of appeal to the Administrative Court of Hesse concerning the prohibition of night flights. 
The Minister of Economy Dieter Posch (FDP) announced that the coalition CDU / FDP had entrusted experts to examine the legal point of view the ruling by the Administrative Court and which is a document containing more than 400 pages. 
The Tribunal of Kassel was justified in a written document that the Land should adapt the regulation concerning the prohibition of night flights in the case or the construction of the runway aterrissage northwest of Frankfurt airport was realized. 
The approval of attérir for 17 aircraft between 11 pm and 5 in the morning, as envisaged by the government of the Land, is not compatible with the legal protection of citizens against air pollution at night. 
The coalition must have decided on 4 January if it wishes to make an appeal in cassation against the judgment. 
The opposition criticism this deadline and tries to put pressure on the government representative for celui-cirenonce to appeal to the federal Administrative court in Leipzig. 
The head of the SPD parliamentary group Torsten Schäfer-Gümbel invites the CDU and FDP to return to their promise made before the elections and which was to ban night flights. Otherwise, it will be condidéré as a total failure to a word. 
It is damn hard to be allowed to keep its word, said the head of the Greens Tarek Al-Wazir in referring to the slogan éléctoral FDP "We want our promises ". 
The Minister Dieter Posch denies the accusations of Schäfer-Gümbel who claims that the Land government tries to authorize still night flights using "avocasserie and roublardises ". 
It takes time to conduct a legal review. 
The coalition does not take a decision on the basis of a "rapid" first impression. 
The decision is legally reliable, said Stefan Müller (FDP). 
The interpretation of the opposition concerning the statements of its fraction on the prohibition of night flights is completely érronée. 
US banks repay the aid 
The big American banks, very affected by the crisis, shedding their ties vis-à-vis the state. 
The Bank of America announced Wednesday that it had fully repaid to the Treasury $45 billion (more than 30 billion euros), corresponding to the aid granted under the rescue plan Tarp. 
The chain of American television CNBC reported in a story that Citigroup was also planning to repay the aid received. 
The Banking institutions seeking to get rid of restrictions, which accompanied the acceptance of money, such as limiting bonuses awarded to leader as the Regulation of higher costs. 
The Bank of Americaa launched a capital increase by The sale of securities to investors who reported $19 billion of fresh money. 
The remainder comes from the coffers of the bank that are met through the sale of several branches of other sectors. 
On Wednesday evening, Kenneth Lewis the Director General of the Bank of America held specifically to thank American taxpayers: the injection of capital has significantly helped to overcome a difficult period. 
The bank had assumed its capacity by buying the investment bank Merrill Lynch at the height of the financial turmoil. 
The Citigroup also plans to get money on financial markets to free themselves from the guardianship of the state. 
The U. S. bank could launch as early as Thursday a capital increase of $20 billion, reported the chain CNBC citing the banking community. 
The spokesman of Citigroup did not wish to comment on this information. 
In June the banks Goldman Sachs, JP Morgan Chase and Morgan Stanley had repaid the public funds they had received. 
Election Accelerated 
Finally it is still spent more quickly than expected. 
Barely two weeks after the dismissal of the current taking the post of chief writer Nikolaus Brender by the board of directors of the German ZDF, the successor is appointed. 
The committee wanted to vote yesterday evening to make the appointment. 
Peter Frey who heads the drafting of ZDF was the odds-on favorite. 
The chain has not wished to confirm - officially - the vote in order not to anticipate the procedure. 
However, it appears that there was also the desire not to further undermine the steward of the ZDF Markus Schächter in case the proposal would not be accepted by the Council of Administration. 
Frey, who is the candidate of Schächter, needed the vote of 9 members of the Commission on 14. 
The result of the vote was not yet known at the end of the drafting of this edition. 
Two weeks ago, Schächter had proposed to the Council of Administration to extend for five years the contract of Nikolaus Brender but this had been rejected. 
Only 7 Council members had expressed support for the continuation of Brender and 7 others had voted against. The dismissal by vote of Brender represented a failure although predictable for Schächter. 
Indeed, the CDU majority in the Council of Administration had already suggested several weeks before the vote, not wanting to renew Brender to his position. 
It is Roland Koch, the Minister-President of the Land of Hesse who had organized a league against the editor. 
He had denied that the contract of esteemed writer in chief is extended, citing the fact that the rate of listening to the news of the ZDF had fallen under Brender. 
That is why protests were still taking place, almost until the vote, denouncing the growing political influence on ZDF. 
At the end there was even 35 experts in public law who had meddled in the debate and who felt that the action of Koch was unconstitutional. 
But it will have achieved nothing. 
Peter Frey: Who is it? 
Peter Frey was born on 4 August 1957 to Bingen. 
He studied the science-policy, pedagogy and Romance languages (Spanish). 
He then worked in radio body Südwestfunk (Rhineland-Palatinate) and the German daily Frankfurter Rundschau (national). 
In 1983 he became editor in the ZDF first the news magazine "heute-journal" (newspaper today). 
