But for the first time, this expression seems to take a practical meaning. 
The accreditation council decided to significantly reduce the number of some reviews: "Each module should normally be concluded by a single review," in a document of 30 pages on future conditions for admission to university cycles. 
Reinhold Grimm, president of the Board of accreditation said that by sharply reducing the burden of reviews should be able to stop the slippage, which interfered considerably to the étudiabilité. 
The "étudiabilité" should also be, in the future, the decisive criterion of the organization of studies. 
The modules like the substance must be examined carefully to see if we cannot avoid this smothering sensation that you feel sometimes in the choice of courses. 
