The case Kunduz 
Frontal attack opposition: the head of the parliamentary group of the Greens, Jürgen Trittin, accused the Minister of Defence Guttenberg of lying in the case of the case Kunduz. 
The SPD and The Left party (Die Linke) asked The Chancellor explanations. 
Hamburg / Berlin - After reviewing the latest information on the air attack in Kunduz, the opposition has criticized the Minister of Defence Karl-Theodor zu Guttenberg (CSU) délibérémentdissimulé some facts. 
The Minister has intentionally "made an untruth" on the deadly strike two tankers last September, said the head of the parliamentary Group of the Greens, Jürgen Trittin, Saturday during the broadcast of information chain ARD "Tagesschau" (the Journal of 20h). 
Clearly, this means that he lied. 
The order to kill has been given in total disregard of the rules of the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan (ISAF). 
It is, in essence, the content of the report available to NATO and which was read by Mr Guttenberg, Trittin said. 
Last Friday, according to new revelations of the media, the objective of lafrappe was in reality, not to destroy the stolen trucks, but was intended to eliminate two important Taliban leaders. 
According to the investigation report of NATO, 142 people were killed or injured in the U.S. air strike which was launched at the request of the German Colonel Goerg Klein, military commander of Kunduz. 
The Greens, the SPD and the Left have requested Saturday Chancellor Angela Merkel (CDU), to decide as soon as possible before the federal parliament and reveal what Guttenberg really knew about the incident. 
Jürgen Trittin and his colleague from the Green Party Renate Künast are of the opinion that Mrs Angela Merkel must say clearly whether the strategy of targeted killing is part of the government's Afghan policy fédéralet if the Chancery, the army and intelligence services have approved this new strategy. 
The government spokesman categorically rejects these criticisms. 
The Chancery has in no way influenced the interventions of the army in Afghanistan, he said. 
