These two dreams were of magnitude. " 
On Louis-Ferdinand Céline: "This writer picked up cry pushed from a bridge by This character of Munch to bring its echo until the bottom of the night of the 20th century, in his literary form, and it did in the brain itself and invoking the postériorité with a speech violate the maggots." 
On Dorothy Parker: "One day it began to knees and prayed:" God, I beg you to do that I constantly write as a woman. " 
On Joseph Conrad: "On his tomb were engraved to Spenser:" Sleep after the effort, / after the storm the port, / the rest after the war, / after life, tired death delights. " 
On Virginia Wolf: "in its baggage she was carrying its depression. 
Her husband accepted very normally it tell him that Edward VII the épiait between the azalées or that birds singing in Greek. 
There has never seen a man as patient and lover of a névrosée whose literary talent exceeded the madness. " 
On Pío Baroja: "What did Martín-Santos if it is to try to conceal Joyce in Baroja? 
That tried Benet if it is to shoot Baroja by Faulkner? 
What did this if it is to suck the glory of this man to serve as a pedestal? " 
A cowardly aggression 
Last week, my mother, who was about 70 years old, was walking in our neighbourhood of the city of Fuenlabrada, when a group of young people between 15 and 18 years spent beside it and our dog, a sang-mélé, saved the spa and not weighing more than six kilos, and without saying a word, they assenèrent two feet who left the dog seriously injured. 
Our indignation is immense because we do not see what is funny to attack a free small animal without defence which, moreover, was on a leash. 
Add to this the indignation of a woman who was walking calmly and which, when it injuria these individuals, came to fear for his physical integrity, since a énergumène which attack an animal is capable of doing the same thing to a woman, a child, an old man or, ultimately, anyone lower than him. 
The episode occurred around 17 p. m., Tuesday as another in a district usually quiet. 
The dog has gémi all day. 
Of course, we have filed a complaint to the police station in the district although we doubt that this serves to much and not to touch the sensitivities, we just want to clarify that the cowardly murderers were Spanish. 
The indignation has led us to denounce this fact. 
We do not understand what is happening in young people to find amusing to mistreat free a defenceless animal which gives us the affection, friendship and is company. 
We do not know where is the good education and respect for animals and people. 
Michelin and Fesvial, sets for helmets 
The tyre manufacturer Michelin, in collaboration with the Spanish Foundation for Road Safety (Fesvial), has launched a campaign to encourage the wearing of helmets, mainly among motorcyclists younger, as indicated today the two structures. 
This initiative aims to raise awareness of the importance of helmets, since it is the only element of protection to avoid injuries to the head, or even death, in the event of an accident in two wheels. 
Michelin indicated that the campaign was in line with his commitment to road safety, which "goes beyond the design and manufacture of products always safer" and said it contributed to this objective by other actions to educational and informative. 
This new campaign of encouragement of helmets in two wheels, under the motto "to be or not to be ", will include a first phase during which posters will be distributed in more than 500 garages of motorcycles, in order to ensure the widest possible dissemination. 
Finally, Michelin has stressed that road safety "is a constant concern" for the company, because as a manufacturer of tyres for two-wheeled vehicles, one of its main objectives is to develop products always safer. 
The sale of light commercial vehicles is progressing 
After nearly two years, the market for light commercial vehicles is beginning to see some light at the end of the tunnel. 
The 9 425 vehicles registered in November in Spain represent an increase of 12.6% compared to 2008 and, more importantly, they represent the first increase after 22 consecutive months of decline, according to figures from the employers' federation of manufacturers Anfac and Ganvam, the dealers. 
However, to qualify the good news, since the reference for comparison, the month of November 2008, was particularly bad, with a decrease of 60% compared to the previous year. 
As a result, despite the rebound last month, registrations accumulated during these 11 months are 40% below those of the previous year. 
Since January, if you add up all vehicles entering the category of light commercial vehicles (derivatives of passenger cars, pickups, vans, light vans and trucks lightweight chassis) 95 853 were sold. 
The big clouds that most affect their application have not dispelled. Indeed, although they are also purchased by individuals, most purchases are made by small or medium-sized enterprises, which pay in almost 100% of cases through an external funding. 
Thus, in addition to the restrictions involved by the limitation of bank loans, other factors such as the increase in the unemployment rate or the persistence of poor economic climate. 
Faced with this situation and the difference of passenger cars, aid for the purchase of the 2000E have little used. 
In addition to individuals, the self-employed and SMEs wishing to acquire a light commercial vehicle of less than 3.5 tonnes with a level of CO2 emissions that does not exceed 160 grams per kilometre, can also benefit, but the number of operations speaks for itself. 
Yesterday, in Ganvam, reminded again the need for the administration to pay particular attention to these vehicles and also to industrial vehicles (trucks and buses). 
The dealers association provides a year 2010 similar to that end, for which she calculates a drop in sales (passenger vehicles and 4x4) of 19%. 
The emergency braking is now mandatory 
As has occurred with the anti-lock brakes ABS and as will take place with the ESP stability control systems, the emergency brake assistance will be a compulsory element on European cars. 
They are already mandatory on passenger cars and light commercial vehicles newly registered, while for the rest of the vehicles a waiting period was set up at the end of February 2011. 
The measure, imposed by the European Union, aims to strengthen the protection of pedestrians, even if, by its mode of action, it can also help prevent many rear shocks. 
The assistant emergency braking is increasing the pressure on the brakes in urgent cases detected by the system through the kick given by the driver. 
But it does not always maintained the pressure until the end. 
According to a study conducted by the manufacturer of components for cars Bosch, a third of drivers involved in an accident had not been able to build on the brakes before the collision, and half of them had not benefited from its full force. 
Up to 1 100 accidents 
The intervention of aid, in revancha, requires the maximum brake system, reducing the distance that the car needs to stop. 
According to a study of the EU, if all cars were equipped with this type of elements, up to 1 100 fatal accidents in which pedestrians are involved could be avoided each year. 
This reduction would be even more important with the popularization of so-called intelligent emergency braking systems: it is calculated that a disaster on four with injured would be avoided. 
In this case, the vehicle is equipped with a system which, thanks to a radar or a camera, detects obstacles and warns the driver, In addition to acting slightly on the brakes. 
If the driver reacts, it aid by increasing the pressure on the pedal, if necessary. 
If it does not react, and although the collision is inevitable, the device carries the maximum effort on the brakes to minimize the damage. 
