The wheel of the Porsche Boxster Spyder 
To design their last and valuable jewellery, engineers are parties of the Porsche Boxster S and managed to the thinning of nothing less than 80 kilograms, leaving the balance to only 1 275 kilograms. 
This has led to happen, first, the automatic roof which has been replaced by a roof bâché manual, to reduce 21 kilos, to employ doors aluminium as those of the GT3, other 15 kilos of less, to remove the air conditioner, 13 kilos, to reduce the gas tank from 64 to 54 litres, 7 kilos of earned, climbing bacquets of sport, still 12 kilos, and with light tires of 19 inches, five kilos. 
Finally, they have relinquished the audio system CDR-30, winning six other kilograms and have replaced the poignéesdes doors by handles in tissues, saving the kilo remaining. 
Although the model also exists with the box PDK dual clutch, the test was carried out on a model to manual box of six speeds, mainly on secondary roads network of California, mountain, with particularly tortuous turns. 
His behaviour can only be described as beyond reproach. 
The weight does not prevent the car from rolling on the ground with aplomb. 
On the contrary: it was a long time that we had not tested a model as small and light, at the same time, guarantees security in the turns, including at high speed. 
It is a small athlete, able to heat its musclesà small speed for the time, until we ask him to sprinter, to curb, recover and grow again its engine... 
It is out what we wanted. Through his leadership, also communicative that, the car will do what will indicate our hands on the steering wheel. 
And it will do so with surgical precision. 
Its engine at will 
The sound of his V6 boxer, with 320 horses (10 more than the Boxster S) is particularly successful and can be strengthened with the option "sport" or through a system that changes the roar of the engine, already used on the Panamera. 
The ability of acceleration is brutal, either to The judgment or during recoveries. 
The suspensions are firm, but not harsh or uncomfortable. 
The roads that we have travelled with the Boyxster Spyder was quite damaged, but the car was well managed potholes. 
The electronic assistants were barely act of presence throughout the journey, while some turns we found ice in the morning and gravel, later in the morning. 
Ultimately, a car ultralégère, more fun to drive and is much more than a simple amendment of the Boxster S. 
The car will be for sale in February 2010, at a price of 70 831 euros. 
