A fine of 63 million to France Télécom to curb competition 
The French competition regulator imposed a fine of 63 million to France Telecom for its anti-competitive conduct in the Caribbean region in the country. 
According to this institution, the operator has limited competition on fixed and mobile telephony by signing exclusive agreements, tariffs and loyalty programs to consumers in the margins of the regulation. 
With this sanction, the former French monopoly and still state-run company, accumulating more than 450 million euros in fines since 1994, because of the obstacles it puts its competitors. 
The sanction imposed yesterday has been increased because the authority which ensures competition considers that France Telecom has committed similar offences in the past and that it is therefore repeat offender. 
A shop applications 
On the other hand, the mobile phone subsidiary of the French company has followed the wake of other operators and opened a shop of Internet applications, with the objective of increasing revenue which do not come from the transmission of voice. 
Initially, the shop applications of Orange will be active in France and the United Kingdom. 
It will wait until 2010 for that it happens in other countries such as Spain. 
Their participation in the Champions League reported 476, 4 million to Real Madrid and Barça since its creation 
The Champions League has become a source of income for clubs, since its birth in 1992. 
Indeed, Real Madrid and F. C. Barcelona won 467, 4 million, which puts them in third and fifth position of clubs who have pocketed the more money in this competition. 
The Manchester United is at the top of the list. 
The Manchester United is at the top of the list. 
Win the UEFA Champions League does not only the glory. It is also one of the main sources of income of big clubs. 
Indeed, competition has allocated 5 362.5 million to 105 teams (including 12 Spanish) who participated in the event since the creation of the tournament, during the 1992 - 93 season, according to information from UEFA. 
The Real Madrid and F. C. Barcelona have been well served in this distribution. 
The club white was the third of the continent to reach the more money for his participation, and the only one, with the A. C. Milan, has won three times the trophy. 
The Catalan club, current taking the title and last winner of the old European Cup in 1992, is fifth on the list. 
At the top of the list are the Manchester United and Bayern Munich, the two teams which, moreover, have billed the more money for their participation in the last Champions League. 
And that, although they have lost before the Barça. 
On the other hand, Spain is only the third country, as regards the money reported by the Champions League, although it has won more titles than any other (five, while Italy has won four, England three and Germany two). 
Distribution 
This apparent paradox is explained by the complex procedure of distribution of money applied by UEFA. 
For this year, the body chaired by Michel Platini expects to earn 1 090 million through the Champions League. 
Of this amount, UEFA will devote 413, 1 million fixed payments: each of the 20 clubs who participated in classification matches (including the Atlético de Madrid) received 2.1 million. 
In addition, those who have managed to participate received 3.8 million just to be there, more than 550 00 euros for each match. 
There is also a bonus in the event of victory (800 000 euros) and equality (400 000 for each team). Those who arrive in eighths of final receive three million each, the eight teams who arrive in a quarter-final reçoivent3, 3 million. 
The last four teams will each receive 4 million. 
And the champion will win 9 million, the 5.2 received by the other finalist. 
Thus, under fixed payments, a club will win at least 7.1 million, and a maximum 31.2 million. 
On the other hand, the Barça pocketed 2.5 million for winning the Super Cup in August. 
But in addition, there are the payments variables, which are enshrined 337.8 million. 
This money is distributed according to the proportional value of each television market. 
The Spanish market is one of the most important, and has four dedicated places. 
The champion of the previous year gets 40% of the money allocated, 30% for the second, 20% for the third and 10% for the fourth. 
The other party will be paid according to the number of matches played during the edition of the year. 
