New tools for the expertise of cars 
In these days of bad weather and accidents, garages are not the only winners. 
Every day, thousands of cars that have suffered a disaster are reduced to a garage, where an expert to assess the damage and the cost of repair. 
Every disaster is different, and the calculation of the cost of parts and labor time can be a long and complex. 
To calculate the cost of compensation of between 20 000 and 30 000 euros, including parts and labor can take two or three hours. 
However, with the assistance of the latest computer tools, it would be a matter of minutes. 
It is for this reason that almost 100% of experts use such systems. 
The Suppliers of services and solutions for the assessment of claims and maintenance are dedicated to the collection of information provided by manufacturers, and then treat them and offer their customers in the form of an useful tool. 
In Spain, Audatex, Solera North American group, is the company leader; 80% of estimates are made with its products. 
Other companies in competition in the field of assessment tools and the development of information on the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax. 
The work with the data provided by manufacturers is far from simple. 
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, the company in Spain with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them their provides information in a different format. 
In addition, the amount of data to treat continues to increase, so that over the past five years, more versions, variants and motors were launched that over the past 15 years. 
When a new car fate on the market, these companies are at work. 
It is a very difficult, because catalogue each thousand pieces of the vehicle and include its price. 
In addition, it establishes a graphic image "smart" of each model on which you can click on the different parts of a passenger vehicle. 
If it is a model sold heavily, the work can be ready in a week if the process moving very quickly. 
If it is a little car sold, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information on 99.2% of cars sold in Spain. 
Among the most exclusive models, they have for example, information on the Porsche, but not the Ferrari or Lamborghini. 
On the vehicles in circulation, the figure exceeds 99%. 
To do the work of documentation and development of databases, Audatex has eight centres across the world (in Spain, France, Germany, the United States, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each of them is specialized in certain brands. 
The national headquarters is located in Alcobendas (Madrid). 
There, more than 100 technicians (usually experts in mechanical) work simultaneously on three screens of computers. 
Audatex invests 90 million every year to develop these databases. 
Each month, 2.5 million data are recorded, and clients receive updates every two days. 
The development of this enormous flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and propose various products. 
The most common application for the repair and maintenance, but in different countries, there are also tools for the management of parts or to calculate the residual sale value or a car. 
The only company that has a guide that provides information on the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax. 
Audatex does not propose in our country, but it is in the United States. 
In view of the products offered by Audatex, it is easy to get an idea of the type of support it can bring to professionals In the sector. 
This company offers 10 different tools, the flagship product being AudaPlus, the standard solution evaluation of claims, for experts. 
There are cars, motorcycles, light and heavy industrial vehicles. 
In addition to the cost of parts, it takes into account the time to repair estimated by the manufacturer or the scales of paint. 
This tool is bought in terms of its use, for each estimate. 
The highest cost is 5.75 euros, for customers who use little, up to 10 times per month. 
Then, each insurance company, which conducts thousands of expertise, negotiates its price with Audatex. 
Other products, such as AudaVIN, allow the identification of a vehicle and equipment with which he came out of the assembly line, only through its chassis number. 
AudaGlass focuses on the glasses of vehicles, and AudaSubastas is open to the professional sector server on the Internet to bid on vehicles reported wrecks. 
Its statistics service is very useful for identifying trends, analyses géo-démographiques or know the common problems by brand or model. 
It is possible to study, for example, how many models of a specific mark went to the garage for a breakdown or how many have suffered serious losses for a given period. 
GT Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of tools. 
It sells, among other things, Gt Estimate, which is also intended to experts and provides digital images, as well as access to documents, price and time official manufacturer. 
GT Motive is a company of the group Einsa, founded in 1971, as a provider of services and solutions for the assessment of claims, breakdowns or maintenance devoiture. 
The guide GT assessment is a historical reference product on the market. 
The company works with 24 000 users in garages, 3 100 experts and 53 insurance companies. 
Its business volume has increased at a rate of 20% per year over the past three years, and has a turnover of EUR 10.8 million in 2008. 
At the beginning of last year, she began the process of internationalization, with the establishment of an office in Paris. 
For its part, Audatex was born in Germany in 1966 and is located in Spain in 1979. 
According to the sources of the company, 62% of its turnover is done in Europe and in the rest of the world, and the remaining 38% in North and South America. It works with 900 insurance companies and 33 000 garages, including 3 000 are in Spain. 
The turnover of global Solera group (Audatex, Sidexa, Informex ABZ, Hollander and IMS) will amount to $557 million, 3.3% more than in 2008. 
In our country, the company will collect 19.1 million, or 7.2% more than last year. 
In 2005, the group Solera was traded 1 000 million, today, its shares are valued at a total of $400 million. 
Since 2007, it is part of the New York Stock Exchange and is part of the benchmark Standard Poor's. 
Internet auction of rugged cars 
Last October, the group Solera purchased Autoonline, an Internet platform for the sale of cars, motorcycles and special vehicles evacuees. 
The operation has involved a cost of 59.5 million for 85% of the company's capital, which could widen next year to 15%. 
The purpose of the acquisition was to provide more value-added services to its customers, with the possibility of access to a huge international market. 
This service to estimate and sale is intended exclusively for professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, experts, leasing companies, garages, the scrapyard and sellers professionals who must be registered before starting to carry out operations. 
This platform was created in 1996 in Germany and manages more than 650 000 operations across Europe, including 500 000 in Germany. 
Among its major markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey. 
There are currently more than 1500 sellers and 4000 experts registered on the site. 
It manages 3, 000 announcements by day and on the Spanish market, 100 new announcements are published every day. 
Under Spanish law, a car whose chassis number was withdrawn can no longer move, but on the other hand, some parts which are not damaged can be used as spare parts. 
The vintage cars can be re-registered, although they have been withdrawn, after complex approaches. 
Specifications of garage in four stages 
With the tool Auda-Taller, the company Audatex ensures that the user gets a quotation in only four steps: identify the vehicle, seek the replacement part, create a quotation and generate. 
The Ease of use is an essential element of these systems, especially to convince the older professionals who, to a greater or lesser extent, are reluctant to the use of new management techniques. 
The database includes 1 034 vehicles, including 666 of tourism, 109, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks. 
Of course, to use a computer and an Internet connection is required. 
Once the model to repair identified through its chassis number, a graphic image of model in question appears then selects the necessary part. 
The user can include variables such as the price of labour, increases or reductions, then it can print the specifications for the client. 
AudaTaller is not a tool to estimate as AudaPlus, but a catalogue of references. 
The main difference between these two systems is that for garages does not include The time of Labour estimated. 
The cost of using this tool for the garage is 350 euros per year, which may be the subject of a credit. 
Currently, the company Audatex works for that these images are in three dimensions. 
It is an innovation that mechanics are a very good eye, as it will, for example, to select a door and turn to see the inner. 
